Pralines & Cream Ice Cream
  --Sohla El-Waylly

2 c (454 g) whole milk
2 c (454 g) heavy cream
6 egg yolks
1 c (200 g) sugar
1/2 tsp Diamond Crystal salt (or 1/4 tsp fine salt)
1 tbsp vanilla paste or extract
1/2 c caramel topping (store-bought or homemade)
1/2 c candied pecans, very roughly chopped (you can find these in the fancy cheese section in the grocery store)

In a medium saucepan (preferably one with sloped sides), bring the cream and milk to a simmer. Meanwhile, in a medium bowl, whisk the yolks, sugar, and salt until thick and pale. Add about half of the hot cream mixture, a splash at a time while whisking, to warm up the eggs. Scrape the egg mixture into the pot of cream. Cook over medium heat, whisking constantly, until steamy and slightly thickened, 3-5 min. (Stop before you see any bubbles; the eggs will curdle.) Whisk in the vanilla, then strain through a fine mesh strainer and chill 24-36 hr. Churn the chilled ice cream base according to your manufacturer’s instructions. Then scrape half the ice cream into a loaf pan. Squiggle over half the caramel and sprinkle over half the nuts. Scrape over the remaining ice mixture, then repeat with the remaining caramel and nuts. Freeze for at least 1 hr before serving.

